
ComputerData <- read.csv (choose.files())

attach(ComputerData)

str(ComputerData)

summary(ComputerData)

pairs(ComputerData)

#Correlation Coefficient matrix - Strength & Direction of Correlation

comp <- lm(price ~ speed + hd + ram + screen + ads + trend + cd + multi + premium, data = ComputerData)
summary(comp)

comp1 <- lm(price ~ ., data = ComputerData)
summary(comp1)

R value for the model comp and comp1 is little bit same. And the coefficient for all the variables are significant.
